'''Lobel''' were slow-moving quadrupeds that naturally produced powerful magnetic fields that impeded the operation of nearby navigation devices and (reportedly) gave pilots headaches.<ref name="card">{{CCG|set=Special Edition Limited|cardname=Lobel}}</ref> Lobels were one of the few [[Species/Legends|species]] that was actually indigenous to the toxic [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Quesh]] though they were also found in small pockets across the galaxy.<ref name="Lobel" /> As a result, their gills were capable of protecting them from the many hazardous liquids found on the planet.<ref name="Calibrations">{{TORcite|exp=lots|type=general|Good Calibrations|Ord Mantell}}</ref> Another adaptation to survive in toxic environments was the lobel's four stomachs. These had a redundancy function where if one stomach was damaged, others could be used for digesting in its stead. Additionally, the Lobel's slow metabolism helped it survive in times of food scarcity.<ref name="Lobel">{{TORcite|type=codex|Lobel}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Lobel was created for use in [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] in [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']], but was left out of the film.<ref name="Star Wars Chronicles">''[[Star Wars Chronicles]]''</ref>

